cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper deals with natural language processing and topic modeling, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the use of a domain-specific knowledge base for automated topic labeling may also fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
